article.description: Joel Bolomboy scored 22 points with 13 rebounds and Weber State handled Portland State 73-58 on Thursday.
article.headline: Bolomboy, Weber State handle Portland State 73-58
article.linkText: Bolomboy, Weber State handle Portland State 73-58
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. -- Joel Bolomboy scored 22 points with 13 rebounds and Weber State handled Portland State 73-58 on Thursday. Bolomboy, second in the nation in rebounding average (13.8), has had double-digit boards in all but one game. He was 10 of 22 from the field as the Wildcats (12-5, 4-0 Big Sky) shot nearly 47 percent. Jeremy Senglin scored 22 points with five 3-pointers and Zach Braxton added 14 points and eight boards. Cameron Forte paced Portland State (6-9, 2-2) with 18 points on 9-of-13 shooting. Isaiah Pineiro added 11 points and seven boards. The Vikings were outrebounded 46-30. McKay Cannon made a layup and 3-pointer at the end of the first half to help Weber State to a 36-29 lead at the break. The Wildcats then started the second half with a 14-2 run and Portland State got no closer than 11 points down the stretch.
